This was a very nice place that had some great food that wasn't to expensive for what it was.  The location is a bit challenging and might be hard to find when looking for it, but once your are in, it is comfortable and relaxing.  The Korean aunties working are all very friendly and attentive.  Service is very quick and they do a good job overall making sure that you are well attended to during you dinning experience.  Menu has a lot of options and a few unique items as well.  Whether you are in the mood for some soup or a sizzling plate of bulgogi, they got it and it is all freshly prepared and very tasty.  My only complaint is that I thought their banchan was rather lackluster.  I am a big banchan fan and view it as a reflection of the Korean restaurant.  It isn't a deal breaker, but does weigh heavy with me especially if I had a bad rest of the meal, but in this case, I did not.  I do recommend this place and would return again to try some of their other dishes.

We decided to check out this place after my husband received a groupon.  The spot was a cute little hole-in-the-wall that surprisingly stays open pretty late. The hours are 10AM - 5AM (virtually unheard of!) but that was definitely a plus as there aren't many food places you can count on to be open past midnight on a weeknight. We came around 7:30PM on a Thursday night and it was not crowded at all.  Parking: wasn't really an issue as we came late in the evening though I suspect it may be more challenging if you come earlier in the day. There were a few stalls to park right in front of the restaurant, although it was a little confusing getting out once we left.  Service/Ambiance: the overall vibe was pretty good. Relatively quiet and homey. The waitress was great-nice and attentive. We had a little trouble understanding her at times, but fortunately, that didn't become an issue and we were able to get exactly what we ordered.  Food: food didn't take too long to come out, which was nice. In terms of taste, it wasn't bad but wasn't great either. It was just okay. I'm not a huge fan of Korean food in general (not really into all of the pickled foods) but I have had better Korean at other spots. The menu was a bit of an issue for me because only the title of the food was in English, the rest was in Korean and we couldn't read what was in it, so we could only make a decision based on the photo and hope it tasted as good as it looked. I ordered the Spicy Beef Soup, which was okay.
